'''Michael Quinn''', [[F.S.C.]] (died March 15, 2009) was an [[United States|American]] [[Roman Catholic]] [[Lasallian Brothers]] and [[psychology]] [[professor]]. Quinn served as the 25th President of [[Saint Mary's College of California]], which was also his [[alma mater]], from 1962 until 1969. Quinn was a 1947 graduate of the college.<ref name=smcc> {{cite news |first=|last=|title=Twenty-fifth Saint Mary’s College President Dies at 86|url=http://www.stmarys-ca.edu/news-and-events/item.html?ID=3170|work=[[Saint Mary's College of California]]|publisher=|date=2009-03-16 |accessdate=2009-04-13}}</ref>
Quinn died on March 15, 2009, at the age of 86.<ref name=smcc/> He was buried at Mont La Salle in [[Napa, California]].<ref name=smcc/>
